    "leafs": {
      "full_name": "Toronto Maple Leafs",
      "league": "NHL",
      "record": "32-36-14",
      "detail": "8th in Atlantic Division",
      "live_strip": null,
      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Leafs",
        "body": "The curtain crashed down on another Toronto Maple Leafs season - a grim 32-36-14 slog that left them <strong>8th in the Atlantic, 31 games back with just 78 points and a seven-game losing streak to cap the misery</strong>. No playoffs, no excuses; this was a roster that sputtered from the jump, bleeding goals and belief in equal measure. The core - Mitch Marner flashing brilliance amid the wreckage, Auston Matthews grinding through injuries that sapped his edge - carried too much freight on shoulders already bowed by expectation. What went wrong? Goaltending crumbled like stale pucks, defense leaked oil, and Craig Berube's bark couldn't mask the bite missing up front. Right? Precious little, save for flashes from kids like Fraser Minten hinting at tomorrow. Now the real skate begins: <strong>draft lottery odds staring at pick 15, free agency whispers around a disgruntled Morgan Rielly, and Berube's seat scorching under Shanahan's glare</strong> - will Treliving swing for a rebuild or double down on the stars? Leafs Nation braces for the purge; summer's the series that counts.",
        "updated": "Updated April 19, 2026"
      },
