    "jays": {
      "full_name": "Toronto Blue Jays",
      "league": "MLB",
      "record": "7-13",
      "detail": "5th in AL East",
      "live_strip": null,
      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Jays",
        "body": "Four losses in four nights - Toronto's bats strangled, bullpen betrayed, and the desert sun baking another defeat into the books. <strong>Corbin Carroll's eighth-inning grand slam off Jeff Hoffman yesterday</strong> turned a 2-2 tie into a 6-2 gut punch from the Diamondbacks, capping 12 hits for the Jays that produced zilch after the third. At 7-13, they're anchored in fifth in the AL East, 5 games back amid a four-game skid that started in Milwaukee and deepened in Arizona - offense sputtering, stranding runners like lost luggage. Hoffman's been a strikeout machine early, but that slam exposed the 'pen's fragility; no fresh injury bites, but the lineup's urgency screams for Vlad Guerrero Jr. to ignite before this road trip buries them. No one's panicking yet - this is April - but the mirror's unkind. <strong>Kevin Gausman takes the hill this afternoon in the series finale at Chase Field</strong>; salvage a win, or stare down a .350 clip staring back. The hunt demands desperation now.",
        "updated": "Updated April 19, 2026"
      },
