        "body": "The draft smoke thickens around Washington, where a 5-12 stumble left them third in the NFC East - six games back, but clutching the No. 7 pick like a lifeline in this rebuild roulette. <strong>Jack Sperry's perfect seven-round mock dropped Saturday</strong>, handing the Commanders WR Makai Lemon to stretch the field, CB Jermod McCoy to lock down receivers, and a late QB Taylen Green as insurance - echoing the buzz from Paul's breakdown eyeing elite playmakers at seven or trade-down gambits for volume. Free agency pruned vets like Deebo Samuel, Austin Ekler, and Von Miller, exposing trenches and secondary gaps that scream for OT Francis Mauigoa or EDGE Arvell Reese if they slide. GM Adam Peters won't chase quick fixes - Jeremiyah Love tempts for instant pop, but long-term trumps band-aids on this flawed roster. Eyes on Harold Perkins Jr. at ILB to ignite the front seven. <strong>With the draft ticking down next week, watch if they pounce at seven or wheel for Day 2 hauls - 2026 contention hinges on it.</strong>",
